<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Germany-Juice     07-07 0117</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Germany-Juice,0120</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>West Germans Are World's Biggest Fruit Juice Consumers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   West Germans may be the world's
greatest beer lovers, but now they're tops in fruit juice
consumption, too.
   According to the Bonn-based Association of German Fruit Juice
Industries, West Germans drank 33.5 quarts of fruit juice per
capita in 1987. This represents an 11-percent increase over 1986
and is the highest worldwide.
   In second place in national juice consumption is neighboring
Switzerland. In 1987, the average Swiss drank 29.6 quarts. Fruit
juice drinking in the United States was given as 27.6 quarts per
capita.
   The West German fruit juice industry had around $1.65 billion in
sales last year, the association reported.
</TEXT>
