<1ST_LINE>r a PM-MurderCharge     07-07 0232</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Murder Charge,0237</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Charged in Murder of Husband Eight Years Ago</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALTAMONT, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who eight years ago told police
two men shot her husband and then raped her has been arrested and
charged with murder in the shooting, officials said.
   Police took Jane Walker Johnson, 30, of Chattanooga into custody
Tuesday and charged her with first-degree murder in the 1980 death
of her husband, Gary Gene Walker, District Attorney Bill Pope said.
   She remained in the Grundy County Jail pending her arraignment
Friday before a Circuit Court judge, Pope said Wednesday.
   Walker, 25, an auto supply salesman, was killed along a road in
Grundy County on Jan. 3, 1980, while making deliveries in a company
van. He was shot three times as he sat in the van, police said.
   Walker's wife told investigators she became sick while riding in
her husband's delivery van, and he pulled over to the side of the
road, where two men attacked the couple.
   Ms. Johnson told police the men shot her husband, then abducted
her. She said she was beaten and raped before they released her on
Interstate 75 in Catoosa County, Ga., police said.
   At the time of the slaying, an auto parts company offered a
$10,000 reward for information about the killing, and police in two
states searched for the men described by the woman as her attackers.
</TEXT>
