<2ND_LINE>BC-Triangle Industries,0134</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Triangle Unit Acquires Parent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Triangle Industries Inc., the world's largest
consumer packaging concern, said its shareholders approved the
acquisition of Triangle by its closely held subsidiary CJI
Industries Inc.
   The resulting company would continue to be called Triangle after
the deal was completed, officials said.
   The acquisition increases to 82 percent the combined voting
shares of Nelson Peltz, Triangle's chairman, and Peter May, the
president. Both men already had controlled a majority of the
company's voting shares before the deal.
   Triangle provides packages for a grocery list of household
products in addition to its copper-wire and cable businesses.
   Triangle acquired National Can Corp. in 1985 and American Can
Co.'s packaging business a year later.
   Its 1987 sales totaled $4.3 billion.
